description: Team RWB community chapters nationwide. Team RWB enriches Veterans' lives by connecting them to their community through physical and social activity.
notes: Data sourced from Team RWB StorePoint chapter locator API
Includes local chapters and state-level coordination groups
Team RWB is free to join for Veterans, service members, and supporters
Weekly fitness activities include running, hiking, yoga, functional fitness
Monthly social events build community and combat isolation
Eagle Leadership Development program available for advanced engagement
Download Team RWB Member App for local event schedules

chapters.name: Charlotte
chapters.description: Welcome to Charlotte, a sprawling city with plenty of adventure to be found. Come join fellow Eagles and explore this beautiful city! We have many Greenways to walk, bike, run or ruck. One Greenway starts at the historic Polk House. Like water adventures, try the US Whitewater Center. Just over the border in SC there is Anne Springs Close Greenway with plenty of hiking trails and adventures for kids including family camp outs. If you like amusement parks we have Carowinds which is located in both NC and SC. Looking for sports teams to cheer for? We have Charlotte FC, the Hornets, Checkers, Knights, and the Carolina Panthers.

chapters.name: Fort Drum / Watertown
chapters.description: In Watertown and Fort Drum, we know the life of a soldier. We are that community of Veterans, soldiers, and supporters embodying the mission of Team RWB. We ask that you embrace the excitement of pushing your limits and the joy of camaraderie with your fellow Eagles. Above all else, you should have fun! Even during challenges, remember that every obstacle is an opportunity and every friendship is a treasure. Let your fire within burn bright, igniting a passion for growth and a love for the journey in all those that you meet.

chapters.description: Welcome to the Team RWB Philadelphia Chapter Group! We love getting outside together across the Philadelphia area - from Center City to the suburbs, to the Jersey shore and everywhere in between. Rucking, hiking, running, monthly missions, local sporting events, and weekly socials are what we like to do - check out the events tab for more details. All fitness levels are welcome. Let's get after some Big Fitness Goals (BFGs) together and have fun in the process! Contact the Chapter Captain if you have an event idea.
